<sec id="sec2.5.2" class="sec">
 <div class="title" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">2.5.2. MICs and MBCs Determination</div>
 <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">The MIC (minimal inhibitory concentration) and MBC (minimal bactericidal concentration) tests were performed (in triplicate) by the broth microdilution method. The essential oils were dissolved in DMSO (Sigma). Serial dilutions (1 : 2) from 2.5% (v/v) as the essential oil concentrations to be incubated at 37°C for 24 h with the bacterial suspensions adjusted to 10
  <span class="sup">5</span> CFU/ml in wells of 96-well microplates (Thermo Fisher Scientific). Untreated control (wells containing bacteria with DMSO at a concentration of 1%) was included in the assay.
 </p>
 <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">After incubation, the wells were optical density examined (OD
  <sub>600</sub> nm) with a spectrophotometer (Multiskan EX) for bacterial growth.
 </p>
